// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// MODEL DATABASE — data quality procedure and field reference
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
//
// ── DATA QUALITY RULES ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
//
// OLLAMA_LIBRARIES is the authoritative list of supported libraries.
// Do NOT add entries to OLLAMA_LIBRARIES unless explicitly instructed.
// MODELS must cover every size variant of every library in OLLAMA_LIBRARIES,
// and must not contain entries for libraries absent from OLLAMA_LIBRARIES.
//
// Every MODELS entry must satisfy ALL of the following:
//
//   1. ollama_tag is verified present in the official ollama library.
//      Entries without a confirmed ollama_tag must not exist in this file.
//
//   2. A verified HuggingFace config.json URL (config_url) must exist and
//      resolve. Architecture parameters are sourced from that file only.
//      If no HuggingFace repo can be found, the model must not be included.
//
//   3. weights_gb and quantization are sourced from the ollama OCI registry
//      manifest (exact values, not estimates).
//
//   4. organization is derived from the HuggingFace repo namespace, mapped
//      through the known-org table below. If the org cannot be identified
//      with confidence, use the HuggingFace namespace as-is.
//
//   5. origin is set ONLY when the organization's country is unambiguous
//      (incorporated company with known HQ). Set to null for community
//      projects, academic consortia, or any case where origin is uncertain.
//
// ── KNOWN ORGANIZATION TABLE ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
//
//   HF namespace            organization            origin
//   ──────────────────────  ──────────────────────  ──────────────
//   meta-llama              Meta                    USA
//   codellama               Meta                    USA
//   mistralai               Mistral AI              France
//   google                  Google                  USA
//   microsoft               Microsoft               USA
//   WizardLM                Microsoft               USA
//   ibm-granite             IBM                     USA
//   CohereForAI             Cohere                  Canada
//   tiiuae                  TII UAE                 UAE
//   nvidia                  NVIDIA                  USA
//   openai                  OpenAI                  USA
//   allenai                 Allen AI                USA
//   bigcode                 BigCode                 International
//   epfl-llm                EPFL                    Switzerland
//   stabilityai             Stability AI            UK
//   upstage                 Upstage                 South Korea
//   LGAI-RESEARCH           LG AI Research          South Korea
//   HuggingFaceTB           HuggingFace             USA
//   TinyLlama               TinyLlama               Singapore
//   LiquidAI                Liquid AI               USA
//   lmsys                   LMSYS                   USA
//   llava-hf                LLaVA                   USA
//   deepcogito              DeepCogito              USA
//   NousResearch            NousResearch            USA
//   teknium                 NousResearch            USA
//   vikhyatk                Moondream               USA
//   SkunkworksAI            SkunkworksAI            null  (community)
//   cognitivecomputations   Cognitive Computations  null  (community)
//   phind                   Phind                   USA
//   Groq                    Groq                    USA
//   defog-ai                Defog                   null  (HQ unconfirmed)
//   Intel                   Intel                   USA
//   jinaai                  Jina AI                 Germany
//   berkeley-nest           UC Berkeley             USA
//   Nexusflow               Nexusflow               USA
//   WizardLM-Research       WizardLM                null  (community)
//   jondurbin               community               null  (community)
//   cloudyu                 community               null  (community)
//
// ── FIELD DEFINITIONS ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
//
// name         : Human-readable model name used in the UI dropdown.
//                Format: "{Model family} {version if relevant} {size}" — e.g.
//                "Llama 3.1 8B", "Mistral 7B v0.3", "Mixtral 8x22B".
//                Use the organization's official naming, append size suffix.
//
// ollama_tag   : Exact tag in the format "{library}:{variant}", where library
//                matches an entry in OLLAMA_LIBRARIES and variant is the size
//                slug as it appears on ollama.com/library/{library} (e.g.
//                "llama3.2:3b", "gemma3:27b"). One MODELS entry per variant.
//
// origin       : Country where the creating organization is headquartered.
//                null if uncertain — shown as "community project" in the UI.
//
// organization : Lab, company, or consortium that trained the model.
//
// moe          : true if the model uses Mixture-of-Experts architecture.
//                Omit for dense models (do not write false).
//
// max_context  : Model's hard architectural context limit in tokens.
//                Source: max_position_embeddings in config.json.
//
// params_b     : Total parameter count in billions.
//                Informational only — not used in any calculation.
//
// params_b_active : Active parameter count per forward pass for MoE models.
//                Omit for dense models (do not write for non-MoE entries).
//                Informational only — not used in any calculation.
//
// weights_gb   : Compressed model size in GB as distributed by ollama.
//                Source: ollama OCI registry manifest (exact layer bytes).
//
// layers       : Number of transformer decoder layers.
//                Source: num_hidden_layers in config.json.
//
// num_attention_heads : Total query heads. Source: config.json.
//                Not used in the KV cache formula — shown for reference only.
//                Used to derive head_dim when not explicitly set in config.json.
//
// num_key_value_heads : KV head count (less than num_attention_heads for GQA).
//                Source: num_key_value_heads in config.json.
//                CRITICAL — used directly in the KV cache formula.
//
// hidden_size  : Embedding dimension. Source: hidden_size in config.json.
//                Used to derive head_dim when config.json has no explicit value.
//
// head_dim     : Size of each KV head vector.
//                Source: head_dim in config.json if explicit (some Mistral and
//                Gemma models set this independently). Otherwise derived as:
//                  head_dim = hidden_size / num_attention_heads
//                CRITICAL — used directly in the KV cache formula.
//
// quantization : GGUF quantization level (e.g. Q4_K_M).
//                Source: ollama OCI registry manifest.
//
// config_url   : Direct URL to the model's config.json on HuggingFace.
//                Must be a live, verified URL.
//
// ── KV CACHE FORMULA ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
//
//   bytes_per_token = layers × num_key_value_heads × head_dim × 2(K+V) × bpe
//   max_ctx = largest power-of-2 ≤ min(available_vram / bytes_per_token, max_context)
//
//   where bpe = bytes per element: f16=2, q8_0=1, q4_0=0.5
//
// ── MAINTENANCE PROCEDURE (run when asked to update models.js) ───────────────
//
// STEP 1 — Verify ollama_tag exists in the ollama library
//   Browse ollama.com/library or run: ollama pull <tag>
//   If the tag is not found, do not include the model.
//
// STEP 2 — Fetch weights_gb and quantization from ollama registry
//   Fetch the OCI manifest:
//     GET https://registry.ollama.ai/v2/library/{model}/manifests/{variant}
//   Sum all layer sizes in bytes, convert → GB: bytes / 1073741824,
//   round to 1 decimal place. The quantization level is in the layer
//   media type string (e.g. "application/vnd.ollama.image.model") filename
//   or readable via: ollama show <tag> (quantization shown in model info).
//
// STEP 3 — Find the HuggingFace config.json
//   Check the ollama model page (ollama.com/library/<name>) for source links.
//   Search HuggingFace for the model name if not linked.
//   Fetch config.json and extract:
//     num_hidden_layers          → layers
//     num_attention_heads        → num_attention_heads
//     num_key_value_heads        → num_key_value_heads
//     hidden_size                → hidden_size
//     max_position_embeddings    → max_context
//     head_dim (if present)      → head_dim (explicit, takes priority over derived)
//   If head_dim absent: head_dim = hidden_size / num_attention_heads
//   WARNING: some Mistral-family and Gemma models have explicit head_dim values
//   that do NOT equal hidden_size / num_attention_heads. Always prefer explicit.
//   NOTE — multimodal (vision-language) models: the KV cache formula applies
//   only to the language backbone. Use the language backbone's config.json.
//   If the top-level config.json contains a "text_config" sub-object, all
//   architecture fields (num_hidden_layers, num_attention_heads, etc.) are
//   inside it — read from there, not from the top level.
//
// STEP 4 — Derive organization and origin
//   Extract HF org namespace from config_url.
//   Map through the known-org table above.
//   If not in the table: use the HF namespace as organization, origin = null.
//
// STEP 5 — Sanity-check the KV formula
//   Compute: layers × num_key_value_heads × head_dim × 4
//   (×4 = ×2 for K+V, ×2 for fp16 bytes)
//   Example — Llama 3.1 8B: 32 × 8 × 128 × 4 = 131,072 bytes/token (128 KB)
//
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Last verified: March 2026
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

// ── CURATED OLLAMA LIBRARY LIST ──────────────────────────────────────────────
// Source: ollama.com/library?sort=popular — 100 selected, March 2026.
// Each value is the URL suffix of https://ollama.com/library/{name}.
// Every library must have one MODELS entry per available size variant.
//
// Legend:
//   ✓  covered — one or more entries exist in MODELS
//   ✗  missing — needs HF config.json research and a MODELS entry
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
